Citation.sTitle: Activity coefficients at infinite dilution of organic solutes in the ionic liquid 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium hexafluoroantimonate using gas liquid chromatography at T = (313.15, 323.15, and 333.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Activity coefficients at infinite dilution were determined for 27 solutes: n-alkanes, alk-1-enes, alk-1-ynes, cycloalkanes, alkylbenzenes, alcohols, and ketones in the ionic liquid 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium hexafluoroantimonate, [BMIM][SbF6], by gas liquid chromatography at three different temperatures, T = (313.15, 323.15, and 333.15) K. The results are compared to published data on related compounds. The partial molar excess enthalpy values at infinite dilution were calculated from the experimental data over the same temperature range. Selectivities and capacities at infinite dilution were calculated for the hexane/benzene and methanol/benzene systems from experimental infinite dilution activity coefficients and compared to the literature values for related ionic liquids, as well as to data on industrial molecular solvents.
